definition: first of the ten Heavenly Stems 十天干[shi2 tian1 gan1]/(used for an unspecified person or thing)/first (in a list, as a party to a contract etc)/letter "A" or roman "I" in list "A, B, C", or "I, II, III" etc/armor plating/shell or carapace/(of the fingers or toes) nail/bladed leather or metal armor (old)/ranking system used in the Imperial examinations (old)/civil administration unit in the baojia 保甲[bao3 jia3] system (old)/ancient Chinese compass point: 75°

sentences.english: The vendor, who also peddles pet turtles, says she is selling more of the stuff these days.
sentences.chinese: 贩售小甲鱼的摊贩告诉我们，她最近卖得比往日好。

sentences.english: I jumped into the water and I was surrounded by reef sharks and red snappers.
sentences.chinese: 我跳入水中，四周环游着珊瑚礁鲨和红甲鱼。

sentences.english: Wandering around in the Viera Wetlands are these Florida Soft Shell Turtles.
sentences.chinese: 这些佛罗里达甲鱼正漫步于维耶拉沼泽地。

sentences.english: Sing her "Turtle Soup, " will you, old fellow?
sentences.chinese: 老伙计，那你就给她唱支‘甲鱼汤’，好吗？

sentences.english: Mr Ma said he dosed his runners on turtle soup and caterpillar fungus.
sentences.chinese: 他让自己的队员食用甲鱼汤和冬虫夏草。

sentences.english: I mean what I say,' the Mock Turtle replied in an offended tone.
sentences.chinese: “我知道我说的意思，”素甲鱼生气地回答。

sentences.english: The research on Extracting and Purification PUFA from turtle oil was studied in this article.
sentences.chinese: 本文研究了甲鱼油中多不饱和脂肪酸的提取与纯化。

sentences.english: The snappers started nibbling at my ponytail, they had never seen humans.
sentences.chinese: 甲鱼开始啃我的马尾辫，之前他们从未见过人类。

sentences.english: Objective To find out if there is Vibrio cholera contamination in short-shelled turtles sold in Hengyang City markets.
sentences.chinese: 目的了解衡阳市城区市售甲鱼中有无霍乱弧菌的感染。

sentences.english: Adult snappers are hunted by humans for their meat.
sentences.chinese: 即便是成年了的甲鱼，也会被人类吃掉。
